text: A topographical map of the Ironjaw Lake area Ironjaw Lake is a lake that is located in south-western Schoolcraft County, Michigan in the Hiawatha National Forest. It is just east of the county line with Alger and just north of the county line with Delta County. Other nearby lakes include Hugaboom Lake, Mowe Lake, Blue Lake, Corner-Straits Chain of lakes, Nineteen Lake, Verdant Lake, and Round Lake. ==See also== *List of lakes in Michigan == References == Category:Lakes of Schoolcraft County, Michigan Category:Lakes of Michigan
